headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton scored 22 points and Myles Turner had 17 points, 10 rebounds and a season-high seven blocks to help the Indiana Pacers pull away from the Memphis Grizzlies 127-113 on...
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacers overcome slow start with 50-point 2nd quarter and pull away from Grizzlies 127-113

headlines.description: — Payton Pritchard made eight 3-pointers and scored 28 points, Jayson Tatum finished with his fourth career triple-double, and the Boston Celtics beat the Philadelphia 76ers 124-104 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pritchard and Tatum lead Celtics to 124-104 win over 76ers

headlines.description: — Paolo Banchero had 36 points, 10 rebounds and five assists as the Orlando Magic rallied from an early 19-point deficit to beat the Atlanta Hawks 114-108 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Paolo Banchero scores 36 points as Magic rally past Hawks 114-108

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 26 points and three Cleveland teammates scored in double figures as the Cavaliers beat the Brooklyn Nets 110-97 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Donovan Mitchell scores 26 points as the Eastern Conference-leading Cavaliers beat the Nets 110-97

events.name: Chicago Bulls at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns had 32 points and 18 rebounds, Jalen Brunson added 22 points and 12 assists and the New York Knicks edged the Chicago Bulls 113-111 in overtime Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Towns and Brunson help Knicks edge Bulls 113-111 in overtime

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo scored 23 points in his return after missing six games with a strained calf and the Milwaukee Bucks rallied for a 116-110 victory over the Los Angeles Clippers on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo returns and Bucks use 4th-quarter rally to beat Clippers 116-110

headlines.description: — Jamal Murray scored 34 points, Nikola Jokic finished an assist shy of his 26th triple-double of the season and the Denver Nuggets extended their winning streak to nine games by holding off the depleted Charlotte Hornets 129-115 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jamal Murray scores 34, Nuggets hold off Hornets 129-115 for their 9th straight win

events.name: Phoenix Suns at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — De'Aaron Fox scored 11 straight points in the final three minutes and finished with 26 as San Antonio beat the Phoenix Suns 120-109 Thursday night, hours after learning Spurs star <a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Spurs beat the Suns 120-109 hours after losing star Wembanyama due to a blood clot in his shoulder

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — LeBron James scored 40 points, including eight straight in a fourth-quarter surge, and Austin Reaves had 32 as the Los Angeles Lakers beat the Portland Trail Blazers 110-102 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron James scores 40 points to lead Lakers past Trail Blazers 110-102
